history.text: Hey, what did you think of the Oscars best picture?
It was awesome. Michael Shannon did an amazing job!
I agree, overall I think most of the acting jobs were great!
I agree. And the critics are right. It is one of "Toro's most stunningly successful works."
I like how it was set in Baltimore in 1962. I wasn't expecting that from the trailer.

Yeah, I didn't think Duillermo del Toro could surpass Pacific Rim but he did a phenomenal
 job here.

Yeah me either, although it did look a bit dated on the trailer
, I was expecting it would take place in the 1920s or something.
I liked how Sally Hawkins' character has a handicap.
Yeah, it made him more personable and charming as a character.
I agree. The romance was great, too
made her I meant, typo
What did you think about the humanoid amphibian?

I thought it was creepy at first but then I was mesmerized\
 by it, like Sally.

She probably connected
 with him because she was an orphan child.

Yeah and he was a bit of an escape from her somewhat mediocre
 life.
meaning she had a lot of problems in her day to day life
Very true. Though, living above a cinema would be nice.
That's true. Although the noise might get annoying in time.
Rent would definitely be cheap!
Especially when you're trying to keep a creature in your bathub!

edit: 
bathtub
Yeah, I can't believe she was daring enough to take him to her place!
I thought that was a very suspenseful part. Did you think they would be discovered?
I really did and the film would've suffered for it.
It reminded me of E.T. a little bit when the creature got sick. Well ... except for the romance part.
Yeah, true. The sickness makes the aliens way more engendering and you just want to do anything possible to help them.

I agree. It made me sad. It was also 
sad about the handlers who got shot.
Yeah, that was unfortunate.
That farewell they tried to have prior to all the action was quite sad too.
Especially, how they tortured Mosenkov.
I agree.
Yeah, he didn't deserve that harsh treatment.
At least there was a "happily ever after" ending.
Yeah and the movie deserved all that critical acclaim, it was fantastic.
Yes. Del Toro should be able to make whatever movie he wants now.
Definitely, he's one of the few star directors that I can name. He'll probably do an indie movie soon.
Thanks for the chat! have a good day
You too!
